      <h2 parentName="article" {...{
        "id": "signing-cookies"
      }}>{`Signing cookies`}</h2>
      <p parentName="article">{`It is possible to sign a cookie to automatically verify its contents when it is received. Since it's relatively easy to spoof HTTP headers, this is a good idea for any information that you do not want someone to be able to fake, like authentication information (see `}<Link to="../sessions" mdxType="Link">{`sessions`}</Link>{`).`}</p>
      <p parentName="article">{`To sign a cookie, provide one or more `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`secrets`}</inlineCode>{` when you first create the cookie:`}</p>
      <pre parentName="article" {...{
        "className": "language-js"
      }}><code parentName="pre" {...{
          "className": "language-js"
        }}><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token keyword"
          }}>{`let`}</span>{` cookie `}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`=`}</span>{` `}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token function"
          }}>{`createCookie`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token punctuation"
          }}>{`(`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token string"
          }}>{`"user-prefs"`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token punctuation"
          }}>{`,`}</span>{` `}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token punctuation"
          }}>{`{`}</span>{`
  secrets`}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`:`}</span>{` `}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token punctuation"
