      <p parentName="article">{`Cookies that have one or more `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`secrets`}</inlineCode>{` will be stored and verified in a way that ensures the cookie's integrity.`}</p>
      <p parentName="article">{`Secrets may be rotated by adding new secrets to the front of the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`secrets`}</inlineCode>{` array. Cookies that have been signed with old secrets will still be decoded successfully in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`cookie.parse()`}</inlineCode>{`, and the newest secret (the first one in the array) will always be used to sign outgoing cookies created in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`cookie.serialize()`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
